text:
Gympie Muster, the ultimate place for lovers of music, food, festivals Published on : Thursday, August 13, 2015
If you love music, food, festivals and camping, the Gympie Muster is the place to be. Held on the last weekend in August in Queensland every year it is a great family getaway.
Come and enjoy a weekend of Australian Mateship and the cream of Australian Country Music. You don’t have to be a country music fan to get your toes tappin’, so give it a go and get ready for one boot scootin’ party.
The Gympie Music Muster will host international superstars Sheppard who this year will be headlining Australia’s largest charitable music and camping festival. The group behind the international runaway hit and Australian #1 single Geronimo will bring their upbeat folk-pop party vibes to the main stage of the 34th Annual Gympie Music Muster, August 27 – 30.
The Gympie Music Muster will be one of a string of major international festivals Sheppard is performing at this year including Rock in Rio (Brazil), Lollapalooza (USA), Summer Sonic (Japan), Isle of Wight (UK), PinkPop (Holland), BBK Live (Spain) and Southside & Hurricane (Germany).
As they say “There are no strangers just friends you haven’t met yet”. So join all in celebrating Australia’s Country Music.
